                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13982216" author="ssc" created="Sun, 27 Apr 2014 08:44:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t the issue that we use slf4j, which allows people to plugin the logging framework of their choice? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13982261" author="smarthi" created="Sun, 27 Apr 2014 09:48:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sebastian that&apos;s correct. But what do we want the default slf4j binding to be for Mahout out of the box - log4j.&lt;br/&gt;
If log4j we need a log4j.xml in Mahout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=andrew.musselman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;andrew.musselman&quot;&gt;Andrew Musselman&lt;/a&gt; log4j.propeties is so 2002, please change this to use log4j.xml .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13984043" author="dlyubimov" created="Tue, 29 Apr 2014 06:46:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I ever used log4j only. How can we configure mahout to clamp down on the log level in the shell with currentn logging approach?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if not, wouldn&apos;t it make sense to create a confg folder with log4j.properties.template in it and add it to the classpath, just like spark does?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13984405" author="andrew.musselman" created="Tue, 29 Apr 2014 16:24:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dlyubimov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dlyubimov&quot;&gt;Dmitriy Lyubimov&lt;/a&gt; Yes, along those lines; need to set it up with a reasonable logging level(INFO?) that can be easily turned to DEBUG while inspecting problems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001010" author="ssc" created="Sun, 18 May 2014 07:15:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=andrew.musselman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;andrew.musselman&quot;&gt;Andrew Musselman&lt;/a&gt; whats the status here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001878" author="andrew.musselman" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 16:18:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Haven&apos;t touched it; overbooked at work the past couple months.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14383098" author="smarthi" created="Fri, 27 Mar 2015 00:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can this be done for 0.10.0 ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14383108" author="andrew.musselman" created="Fri, 27 Mar 2015 00:55:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to say yes but my experience with logging is it can be a can of worms.  Let&apos;s try but might punt to .1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
